A 20-year-old student has been found shot dead in a quiet Texas street after reportedly heading  to a party alone.

Trey Alan Kurtz's body was found at an intersection in Brenham on Thursday night after someone driving through the area spotted it and called 911.

Authorities have not arrested anyone and are now appealing for information in a case that has left the 20-year-old student's friends and family heartbroken.

Kurtz, from West Houston, had started classes at Blinn College this semester - after years of battling epilepsy and multiple surgeries, his father said.

