Alan Kurtz told Click2Houston that his son was finally himself again and ready to start school, so they picked a campus close to home. But just months later, tragedy struck.

Now he is trying to find out what had happened to his youngest son, whom he called 'my best friend'.

'From what I heard, his roommate wanted to go to a party or something, and roommate decided not to [but Kurtz] decided to go to it and was walking over there,' Mr Kurtz told the channel.

'I don't know if he got in a scuffle or a fight and someone pulled a gun on him, or if it was a drive by. I don't know.

'All I know is that someone took a big piece of my life away from me that can't be replaced.'

Investigators told News3 that Kurtz dies of a single gunshot wound, but would not say where on his body he had suffered the wound. 

