A witness told police they heard what sounded like a gun shot in the area about an hour before the student's body was found, KWTX reported.

A car was also seen speeding east on Seelhorst just after the shot was heard.

His body was found more than a mile from his college and he did not have his car, witnesses said.

The body has been taken to the Travis County Medical Examiner in Austin for an autopsy.

No one has been arrested in the case and investigators are urging anyone with information to contact police in Brenham. 

'We're going to do everything we can to make sure this case gets solved,' Brenham Police Chief Rex Phelps said.

Friends remembered Trey as a sweet friend and a sports fanatic, who had been on his school wrestling team and loved playing baseball, football and soccer. 

